        "3. **Price distribution** — the histogram and KDE tell us whether the price data is normally distributed (important for understanding ARIMA residual assumptions)\n",
        "4. **Monthly box plots** — reveal within-month spread and any seasonal effects\n",
        "5. **Daily returns (log differences)** — financial time series are often more stationary in log-return space; useful context\n",
        "\n",
        "Observing these patterns will directly explain our stationarity test results in Section 3."
