        "## 5. ARIMA Model — Grid Search over (p, d, q)\n",
        "\n",
        "### 5.1 What is ARIMA?\n",
        "\n",
        "ARIMA stands for **AutoRegressive Integrated Moving Average**, a classical statistical framework for modelling and forecasting univariate time series. The model has three components:\n",
        "\n",
        "- **AR(p)** — AutoRegressive: the current value `yₜ` is modelled as a linear combination of the previous `p` values (`yₜ₋₁, yₜ₋₂, …, yₜ₋ₚ`) plus an error term. This captures the momentum or inertia in the series.\n",
        "\n",
        "- **I(d)** — Integrated: the series is differenced `d` times to remove stochastic trends and achieve stationarity. For our data, d=1 (confirmed in Section 4).\n",
        "\n",
        "- **MA(q)** — Moving Average: the error at time `t` is modelled as a linear combination of the previous `q` error terms (`εₜ₋₁, …, εₜ₋ₚ`). This captures any short-term shock effects that persist for `q` periods.\n",
        "\n",
        "The full model equation is:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\phi(B)(1-B)^d y_t = \\theta(B)\\varepsilon_t$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where `B` is the backshift operator, `φ(B)` is the AR polynomial, and `θ(B)` is the MA polynomial.\n",
        "\n",
        "### 5.2 Model Selection via AIC (Akaike Information Criterion)\n",
        "\n",
        "Rather than manually selecting (p, d, q) based solely on the ACF/PACF plots (which requires expert judgment), we perform an exhaustive **grid search** over all combinations in:\n",
        "- `p ∈ {0, 1, 2, …, 8}` — 9 values\n",
        "- `d ∈ {0, 1, 2}` — 3 values  \n",
        "- `q ∈ {0, 1, 2, …, 8}` — 9 values\n",
        "\n",
        "This gives **243 combinations** to evaluate. Each is scored by the **AIC (Akaike Information Criterion)**:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\text{AIC} = 2k - 2\\ln(\\hat{L})$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where `k` = number of model parameters and `L̂` = maximised log-likelihood. AIC penalises model complexity — a lower AIC means a better balance of fit quality and parsimony. We select the model with the **minimum AIC**.\n",
        "\n",
        "> ⚠️ **Computational Note:** Running 243 ARIMA fits on 500+ observations takes several minutes. Progress is printed every 50 iterations."
      ]
