        "\n",
        "### 6.2 Why Residual Diagnostics Are Critical\n",
        "\n",
        "A well-fitted ARIMA model should leave **residuals that look like white noise**: zero mean, constant variance, and no remaining autocorrelation. If the residuals show:\n",
        "- **Remaining autocorrelation** → the model has failed to capture all temporal patterns; p or q may need to be higher\n",
        "- **Non-normal distribution** → extreme events are present; predictions may be poorly calibrated\n",
        "- **Heteroscedasticity** → the variance is not constant; a GARCH extension may be warranted\n",
        "\n",
        "We use three complementary diagnostics:\n",
        "1. **ACF of residuals** — should show no significant spikes beyond lag 0\n",
        "2. **Histogram and Q-Q plot** — should show an approximately normal distribution\n",
        "3. **Ljung-Box test** — a formal statistical test for residual autocorrelation"
