      "source": [
        "## 8. Part 2 — Facebook Prophet: Alternative Model\n",
        "\n",
        "### 8.1 Literature Review & Motivation\n",
        "\n",
        "**Why Prophet?**\n",
        "\n",
        "Facebook Prophet (Taylor & Letham, 2018) is a decomposable time series model designed for **business forecasting** with the following key properties that make it particularly suitable for this oil price dataset:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **Additive trend model with changepoints**: Prophet models the trend as a piecewise-linear or logistic growth function, automatically detecting **changepoints** — moments where the trend direction shifts. Our data exhibits a clear trend reversal (rise then decline), making this a strong advantage over ARIMA's fixed differencing approach.\n",
        "\n",
        "2. **Seasonality decomposition**: Prophet explicitly models **yearly, weekly, and daily seasonalities** using Fourier series, which ARIMA completely ignores.\n",
        "\n",
        "3. **Robustness to missing data and outliers**: Unlike ARIMA which requires a complete, regular time series, Prophet handles gaps and extreme values gracefully.\n",
        "\n",
        "4. **Uncertainty quantification**: Prophet generates forecast uncertainty via Monte Carlo simulation, producing credible intervals that account for parameter uncertainty — arguably more principled than ARIMA's analytical intervals.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Academic References:**\n",
        "- Taylor, S.J. & Letham, B. (2018). *Forecasting at scale*. The American Statistician, 72(1), pp.37–45.\n",
        "- Cerqueira, V. et al. (2020). *Evaluating time series forecasting models: an empirical study on performance estimation methods*. Machine Learning, 109, pp.1997–2028.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Comparison to ARIMA:**\n",
        "| Property | ARIMA | Prophet |\n",
        "|---|---|---|\n",
        "| Trend | Differencing (d) | Piecewise linear / logistic |\n",
        "| Seasonality | Limited (SARIMA) | Fourier components |\n",
        "| Changepoints | None | Automatic detection |\n",
        "| Interpretability | Moderate | High |\n",
        "| Uncertainty | Analytical | Monte Carlo |\n",
        "\n",
        "### 8.2 Model Formulation\n",
        "\n",
        "Prophet decomposes the time series as:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$y(t) = g(t) + s(t) + h(t) + \\varepsilon_t$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where:\n",
        "- `g(t)` = trend function (piecewise linear by default)\n",
        "- `s(t)` = seasonal components (Fourier series)\n",
        "- `h(t)` = holiday effects (not used here)\n",
        "- `εₜ` = noise term"
      ]
    },
