        "### 8.3 Hyperparameter Tuning\n",
        "\n",
        "Unlike ARIMA where we searched over `(p, d, q)` via grid search, Prophet's key tunable parameters are:\n",
        "\n",
        "- **`changepoint_prior_scale`** (λ): Controls how flexible the trend is. Higher values allow more abrupt trend changes (risk of overfitting); lower values produce smoother trends (risk of missing genuine trend shifts). Range: [0.001, 0.5]\n",
        "\n",
        "- **`seasonality_prior_scale`**: Controls the flexibility of seasonality components. Default (10.0) usually works well.\n",
        "\n",
        "- **`n_changepoints`**: Number of potential changepoints to consider. Default is 25, placed in the first 80% of the training data.\n",
        "\n",
        "We tune `changepoint_prior_scale` using a time-series cross-validation approach — critical because random k-fold CV would violate temporal causality."
      ]
